  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Teenage Pregnancy, SGBV (Sexual and Gender Based Violence) Services, Advocacy and Coordination</narrative>
  </title>
  <description>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Activities under this budget line were devised to reduce the extremes of gender equality that exist in Sierra Leone, reinforced by the Irish Aid programme&#x2019;s role in leading coordination of international partners&#x2019; policy and advocacy actions on gender equality, in particular on the issue of teenage pregnancy and pregnant teenage girls&#x2019; access to education.</narrative>
  </description>
  <description type="2">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Improve adolescent girls&#x2019; access to sexual and reproductive health services and commodities, including for gender and sexual based violence; &#x2022; Contribute to a reduction in the number of teenage pregnancies in line with the Government&#x2019;s National Strategy; &#x2022; Ensure the rights of adolescent pregnant girls to access formal education; &#x2022; Strengthening gender equality advocacy</narrative>
  </description>
